label.value: receptor-mediated endocytosis involved in cholesterol transport

value.value: A receptor-mediated endocytosis process involved in intracellular cholesterol transport.
The directed movement of cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3-beta-ol, or cholesterol-containing compounds, by membrane-bounded vesicles.
The directed movement of cholesterol, cholest-5-en-3-beta-ol, or cholesterol-containing compounds, from the lysosome to the endoplasmic reticulum.

label.value: low-density lipoprotein particle disassembly involved in cholesterol transport

value.value: The disassembly into constituent parts of the low-density lipoprotein particle in the lysosome that contributes to cholesterol transport.

label.value: cholesterol ester hydrolysis involved in cholesterol transport

value.value: The cholesterol metabolic process in which cholesterol esters are hydrolyzed into free fatty acids and cholesterol in the lysosome that contributes to intracellular cholesterol transport.
The polysaccharide-based coating on the inner side of a lysosomal membrane. It may be involved in protecting the membrane from digestion by lysosomal enzymes.

label.value: cell-cell adhesion involved in synapse maturation

value.value: The attachment of the pre-synaptic cell to the post-synaptic cell via adhesion molecules that contributes to synapse maturation.

label.value: protein-containing complex assembly involved in synapse maturation

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a protein complex that contributes to synapse maturation.

label.value: positive regulation of synapse maturation by synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that increases the extent of synaptic maturation as a result of the communication from a pre-synaptic cell to a post-synaptic cell across a synapse.
Any process that modulates the extent of synapse maturation, the process that organizes a synapse so that it attains its fully functional state.
Any process that increases the extent of synapse maturation, the process that organizes a synapse so that it attains its fully functional state.
The process in which the population of cells that make up a tissue undergo directed movement.
The process in which the population of cells that make up a mesenchyme undergo directed movement.
The process in which the population of cells that make up an epithelium undergo directed movement.
The process in which the population of cells that make up a mesendoderm undergo directed movement. The mesendoderm is the epithelial tissue that gives rise to both mesoderm and endoderm.

label.value: cell migration involved in mesendoderm migration

value.value: The orderly movement of epithelial cells from one site to another that contributes to the migration of mesendodermal tissue.
The formation of daughter actin filament branches at an angle on the sides of preexisting mother filaments.
The attachment of an epithelial cell to another epithelial cell via adhesion molecules.

label.value: epithelial cell-cell adhesion involved in epithelium migration

value.value: The attachment of an epithelial cell to another epithelial cell via adhesion molecules that contributes to epithelium migration.

label.value: regulation of actin cytoskeleton organization by cell-cell adhesion

value.value: Any cell-cell adhesion process that modulates the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.
A process in which mitochondrial chromosomal DNA and associated proteins organize into a compact, orderly structure.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of mitochondrial fission. Mitochondrial fission is the division of a mitochondrion within a cell to form two or more separate mitochondrial compartments.

Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of mitochondrial fission. Mitochondrial fission is the division of a mitochondrion within a cell to form two or more separate mitochondrial compartments.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the nucleoid. The nucleoid is the region of a bacterial cell, virion, mitochondrion or chloroplast to which the DNA is confined.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the mitochondrial nucleoid. The mitochondrial nucleoid is the region of a mitochondrion to which the DNA is confined.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the separation of a single continuous membrane into two membranes.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the separation of a single continuous mitochondrial membrane into two membranes and contributes to mitochondrial fission.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to membrane

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in a membrane.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to mitochondrial membrane

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in the mitochondrial membrane.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to mitochondrial membrane involved in mitochondrial fission

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in the mitochondrial membrane that contributes to mitochondrial fission.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of sphingolipid biosynthesis. Sphingolipid biosynthesis is the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of sphingolipids, any of a class of lipids containing the long-chain amine diol sphingosine or a closely related base (a sphingoid).

label.value: positive regulation of sphingolipid biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of sphingolipid biosynthesis. Sphingolipid biosynthesis is the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of sphingolipids, any of a class of lipids containing the long-chain amine diol sphingosine or a closely related base (a sphingoid).

label.value: negative regulation of sphingolipid biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of sphingolipid biosynthesis. Sphingolipid biosynthesis is the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of sphingolipids, any of a class of lipids containing the long-chain amine diol sphingosine or a closely related base (a sphingoid).
A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of sphingolipids within a cell.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an endoplasmic reticulum membrane.

label.value: sphingolipid biosynthesis involved in endoplasmic reticulum membrane organization

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of sphingolipids that contributes to endoplasmic reticulum membrane organization.
The directed movement of substances from the Golgi to lysosomes.
The formation of a continuous ribbon of interconnected Golgi stacks of flat cisternae.
The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization of an epithelial cell.

label.value: establishment of epithelial cell planar polarity

value.value: The specification and formation of the polarity of an epithelial cell along the plane of the epithelial tissue.
The asymmetric formation of a continuous ribbon of interconnected Golgi stacks of flat cisternae that contributes to the establishment of epithelial cell polarity.

label.value: regulation of secretion by asymmetric Golgi ribbon formation

value.value: The asymmetric formation of a continuous ribbon of interconnected Golgi stacks of flat cisternae that modulates the controlled release of a substance from a polarized epithelial cell.
A cellular process that results in the breakdown of a Golgi apparatus that contributes to Golgi inheritance.
Any process in which disassembled Golgi vesicles are localized into daughter cells upon cell division.
The reformation of the Golgi following its breakdown and partitioning contributing to Golgi inheritance.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of spindle assembly. Spindle assembly is the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the spindle, the array of microtubules and associated molecules that serves to move duplicated chromosomes apart.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of Golgi inheritance. Golgi inheritance is the partitioning of Golgi apparatus between daughter cells at cell division.

The process in which the structures of a chondrocyte are generated and organized. This process occurs while the initially relatively unspecialized cell is acquiring the specialized features of a chondrocyte.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of synaptonemal complex assembly. Synaptonemal complex assembly is the cell cycle process in which the synaptonemal complex, a structure that holds paired chromosomes together during prophase I of meiosis and that promotes genetic recombination, is formed.
The joining of two lipid bilayers to form a single organelle membrane.
